Package com.kraken.krakenhax

Class Action

java.lang.Object
com.kraken.krakenhax.Action
All Implemented Interfaces:
android.os.Parcelable
public class Action extends Object implements android.os.Parcelable
Represents an action taken by a user in the app or some event that has occurred to the user.

Instances are stored in Firestore and shown in user profile history lists. This class is a plain data object (POJO) with a public no-argument constructor required for Firestore deserialization. It also implements Parcelable so instances may be passed between Android components via Intent extras or saved/restored in bundles.

Fields: - action: human-readable description of the action (for example "joined waitlist"). - associatedUserID: optional ID of another user related to this action. - associatedEventID: optional ID of an event related to this action. - timestamp: time when the action occurred (Firebase Timestamp).
